01/06/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- On Saturday (31 May) an IMF delegation completed the fifth review of the country's stand-by agreement.
Led by the chief of the Fund's Turkey desk, Juha Kahkonen, the delegation concluded that structural reforms are being delayed and urged Turkey to implement its economic programme more strictly.
Meanwhile, World Bank Vice President Johannes Linn expressed satisfaction Saturday with Turkey's recovery from its severe economic crisis over the past few years.
Linn spoke at the end of a three-day visit to assess current loans by the Bank.
(Hurriyet, Milliyet - 01/06/03;
Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2, AFP - 31/05/03)
